      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_boost_converter_1acbfb668d7b4cfa39aa1a5a5dac3c0e7e" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Boost converter task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function enters the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eTimerExpired: On timer expiry the pointer pElem will be set to 0, to prevent releasing the message because it is allocated static. Finally boost converter is switched off by calling function <ref refid="class_boost_converter_1a2f241b422ebdbd7a570178ceaebdd2fa" kindref="member">off()</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eResume: On reciving the resume message from power manager the timeout value for the maximum activation time period will be extracted from message payload and the timer will be started with this timeout value. Afterwards boost converter is switched on by calling function <ref refid="class_boost_converter_1af5a2f93105e0a24634af5793d2c5c5b8" kindref="member">on()</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eSuspend: On reciving the suspend message from power manager, timer will be stopped and boost converter is switched off by calling function <ref refid="class_boost_converter_1a2f241b422ebdbd7a570178ceaebdd2fa" kindref="member">off()</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eBoostOnReq: Boost converter will be enabled by setting flag isEnabled to true and file BOOST_ENABLED_FILENAME will be written to file system as persistent indication.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eBoostOffReq: Boost converter will be enabled by setting flag isEnabled to false and file BOOST_ENABLED_FILENAME will be deleted. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
